---
description: Enforce org/auth path safety and role test matrix for major changes
alwaysApply: true
---

# Org And Auth Guardrails

- For any change touching Firebase, stores, onboarding, roles, or permissions, verify the organization path is consistent end-to-end: `users/{uid}.organizationId` -> resolved org id -> `organizations/{orgId}/...`.
- Never assume super admin only. Validate behavior for super admin, admin, manager, and operative before declaring a fix complete.
- For Firestore rules changes, update both `website/firestore.rules` and `Project Planner/firestore.rules`, then explicitly state which file is deployment source of truth.
- Avoid introducing stricter rule logic in one subcollection than sibling org subcollections unless explicitly required and documented in the PR notes.
- On permission failures, prefer non-destructive fallback behavior in app code: keep existing data in memory, try cache fallback, and show actionable non-blocking errors.
- Before finalizing major changes, run and report a role matrix check:
  - Can each role read required org collections?
  - Can each role perform intended writes for their flow?
  - Do denied actions fail with clear user-facing messages?
- If a fix is temporary/emergency, label it clearly and include a follow-up tightening step.
